column59:
Here we have a player with huge potential that needs to be worked on. For example his movement off the ball is ok for his level but for Super League he needs some improvement.
In my opinion, he is not ready for Super League yet as he needs to adapt and improve in certain areas but he is very dangerous in the attacking phase. He currently has 9 goals in 12 matches, playing U19, it is a different level but his characteristics cant go unnoticed. 
The idea of a move to Servette is for him to become a better player and I know for sure you guys will make substantial gains from a future sale. I believe it makes more sense for him to go to U21 from January so that you can adapt him to your system and he can get used to the country. It is more realistic to say that he will be ready to play games in the season 24/25. 
Just to let you know that some other clubs in Europe are keeping tabs on him.
